Detailed Incident Register
Incident # | Date       | Employee Name      | Employee ID | Department      | Incident Type | Description
001        | 2024-01-14 | Sarah Mitchell     | EMP-1042    | Packaging       | Injury        | Employee strained lower back while lifting a 45-lb box from conveyor line. Taken to urgent care; returned to work with restriction on lifting >15 lbs for two weeks.
002        | 2024-02-03 | James O'Connor     | EMP-2156    | Warehouse       | Near-Miss     | Forklift operator (Tom G.) swerved to avoid a loose pallet jack; pedestrian (O'Connor) stepped back into racking. No contact. Operator received refresher training.
003        | 2024-02-22 | Rebecca Lin       | EMP-3210    | Administration   | Hazard Report | Flickering fluorescent light fixture in Hall 3 caused reported headaches. Electrician replaced ballast; no injury.
004        | 2024-03-11 | David Everett      | EMP-0723    | Maintenance     | Injury        | Lacerations to right hand from broken glass while replacing window pane in Lab 2. Required 4 stitches; no lost time.
005        | 2024-03-29 | Maria González     | EMP-4388    | Packaging       | Near-Miss     | Automated pallet wrapper activated unexpectedly while employee was adjusting film roll. Sensor override button was not engaged. Machine locked out and procedure updated.
006        | 2024-04-05 | Chris Tomlin       | EMP-5420    | Shipping        | Injury        | Trip and fall on uneven floor grating in loading dock area. Bruised left knee. First aid applied; returned to full duty.
007        | 2024-04-18 | Nneka Okafor       | EMP-6673    | Laboratory      | Hazard Report | Employee noticed chemical odor near fume hood exhaust vent. Shut down hood; industrial hygiene sampling confirmed volatile organic compound leakage from a worn gasket. Replaced gasket and recalibrated monitors.
008        | 2024-05-09 | Kevin Strathmore   | EMP-1899    | Warehouse       | Injury        | Struck by falling case of canned goods from height of 6 feet during order picking. Contusion on shoulder. Medical evaluation; no fracture. Lost one full day.
009        | 2024-05-22 | Angela Rice        | EMP-9053    | Administration   | Hazard Report | Loose carpet edge in corridor outside HR office caused trip hazard. Facilities secured carpet same day.
010        | 2024-06-07 | Luis Ortiz         | EMP-7731    | Maintenance     | Near-Miss     | Lockout/tagout procedure bypassed on conveyor motor for cleaning. Motor started briefly when cleaning stick contacted start switch. No injury. Disciplinary action and retraining conducted.
011        | 2024-06-25 | Patricia Navarro   | EMP-4982    | Shipping        | Injury        | Heat stress symptoms (dizziness, nausea) during outdoor container loading in 98°F index. Treated in cooling station; returned to duty after 30-minute rest. Hydration policy reinforced.
012        | 2024-07-14 | Jamal Hicks        | EMP-3409    | Warehouse       | Injury        | Puncture wound to left palm from exposed nail on wooden pallet. First aid (cleaning, bandage); tetanus shot administered. Pallet quarantined and removed from circulation.
013        | 2024-08-02 | Yuki Tanaka        | EMP-1554    | Packaging       | Hazard Report | Slippery residue from spilled adhesive on floor near labeling machine. Cleaned immediately. Investigated root cause: cracked container. Spill kit restocked.
014        | 2024-08-19 | Robert Dunne       | EMP-8832    | Warehouse       | Near-Miss     | Overhead door closed prematurely while forklift was exiting, scraping the mast. No personnel near door. Safety sensor adjustment required; door taken out of service until repaired.
015        | 2024-09-06 | Fatima Hassan      | EMP-5678    | Laboratory      | Hazard Report | Autoclave steam leak observed during cycle. Shut down; no injuries. Gasket and pressure relief valve replaced. QA cleared after pressure test.
